osed containers are legacy/backfill cases only, not the normative path for new decomposition.\n- Keep legacy dead-intermediate and historical cleanup wording intact where it describes already-existing open containers.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change agent prompt code, generated skill references, lifecycle implementation, or tests; those are separate child beads under ddx-e9542e0d.\n- Do not drain or close existing historical decomposed queue entries.\n- Do not implement parent/ancestor dependency doctor repair from ddx-130cf9ab.\n\nPARENT AND DEPS\nParent: ddx-e9542e0d.\nDeps: No deps.\nAccept:   1. `docs/triage/decomposition.md`, `docs/beads.md`, `docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md`, `docs/helix/02-design/solution-designs/SD-025-task-execution-lifecycle.md`, `docs/helix/02-design/adr/ADR-023-bead-lifecycle-quality-policy.md`, `docs/helix/02-design/adr/ADR-024-power-escalation-and-review-routing.md`, and matching `docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md` decomposition text state that a lossless child/sibling/replacement decomposition closes the decomposed bead as completed-by-decomposition.\n2. The same docs state that historical open `execution-eligible=false` decomposed containers are legacy/backfill only, not the normative path for new decomposition.\n3. No updated normative decomposition passage says new lossless decomposition should keep the parent open with child dependency edges.\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... -run 'TooLargeDecomposed|DecomposeDoesNotSelfDep|PostAttemptTooLargeNoChanges|PostLadderExhaustion_TriggersDecompose|AutoDecomposeEpic|parent_ancestor_in_deps' -count=1` passes.\n5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\nCreated:  2026-06-17 19:58:21\nUpdated:  2026-06-17 19:58:21\nspec-id: FEAT-010\n"}}
