item_35","output":"ID:       ddx-919bb1a1\nTitle:    agent: update step-zero decomposition instructions\nType:     task\nStatus:   open\nPriority: 0\nLabels:   area:agent, area:bead-lifecycle, area:decomposition, kind:bug, kind:correctness, phase:iterate, prevention, related:ddx-130cf9ab, spec:FEAT-010, spec:TD-031\nParent:   ddx-e9542e0d\nDesc:     PROBLEM\nAgent-facing Step 0 decomposition instructions still say the current bead cannot be closed and only allow a parent-note update during decomposition. That makes the operational answer ambiguous when an agent performs a lossless split: the decomposed bead should be completed by decomposition, and children must not depend on the parent.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- .agents/skills/ddx/reference/work.md:210-213 and .claude/skills/ddx/reference/work.md:210-213 forbid `ddx bead close \u003cbead-id\u003e` for the current bead and only allow `ddx bead update \u003cparent-id\u003e --notes 'decomposed into \u003cchild-ids\u003e'` during Step 0 decomposition.\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go contains the generated execute-bead instruction text that is rendered into prompt snapshots, so the same stale rule reaches launched agents.\n- cli/internal/agent/testdata/execute_bead_prompt_snapshots/agent.txt and cli/internal/agent/testdata/execute_bead_prompt_snapshots/claude.txt lock the old prompt wording unless updated with the source instruction text.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Update .agents/skills/ddx/reference/work.md and .claude/skills/ddx/reference/work.md so Step 0 says agents may file child/sibling/replacement beads, wire only child-to-child or sibling/replacement dependencies, must not add the parent as a child dependency, and may close the decomposed parent once the split is lossless and durable.\n- Update cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go with the same Step 0 decomposition contract.\n- Refresh cli/internal/agent/testdata/execute_bead_prompt_snapshots/{agent,claude}.txt from the source prompt text and keep/update prompt guardrail tests so drift is caught.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change lifecycle code or tracker store behavior; implementation paths are separate child beads.\n- Do not hand-edit `.ddx/beads.jsonl` or generated plugin payloads under `.ddx/plugins/`.\n- Do not change Fizeau routing, provider/model selection, or power escalation policy.\n\nPARENT AND DEPS\nParent: ddx-e9542e0d.\nDeps: No deps.\nAccept:   1. `.agents/skills/ddx/reference/work.md`, `.claude/skills/ddx/reference/work.md`, and `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go` state that Step 0 decomposition may close the decomposed parent after filing a lossless durable split.\n2. The same files state that generated children must use `Parent=\u003cdecomposed-id\u003e` only as hierarchy metadata and must not add the decomposed parent as a dependency; only child-to-child or sibling/replacement dependency edges may be wired.\n3. `cli/internal/agent/testdata/execute_bead_prompt_snapshots/agent.txt` and `cli/internal/agent/testdata/execute_bead_prompt_snapshots/claude.txt` match the updated prompt source.\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run 'TestExecuteBeadPromptSnapshots|TestExecuteBeadPromptSnapshotsUseParentToChildDecompositionEdges' -count=1` passes.\n5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\nCreated:  2026-06-17 19:58:50\nUpdated:  2026-06-17 19:58:50\nspec-id: FEAT-010\n"}}
