io/bin:/home/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/.lmstudio/bin\",\"attempt_id\":\"20260617T195546-6fe14552\",\"base_rev\":\"fef4ec6c0f9b2d542f1837e943ebbba28333782b\",\"bead_id\":\"ddx-e9542e0d\",\"bundle_path\":\".ddx/executions/20260617T195546-6fe14552\",\"prompt_file\":\".ddx/executions/20260617T195546-6fe14552/prompt.md\",\"prompt_sha\":\"346b2886e82d156ad421442bfc385030aec14736b5653afed5c3b5fe87e9ce08\",\"session_id\":\"eb-9610046b\",\"worker_id\":\"\"},\"data\":{\"id\":\"item_36\",\"output\":\"ID:       ddx-ef2c9652\\nTitle:    agent: close parent after pre-claim decomposition\\nType:     task\\nStatus:   open\\nPriority: 0\\nLabels:   area:agent, area:bead-lifecycle, area:decomposition, kind:bug, kind:correctness, phase:iterate, prevention, related:ddx-130cf9ab, spec:FEAT-010, spec:TD-031\\nParent:   ddx-e9542e0d\\nDesc:     PROBLEM\\nThe pre-claim `too_large_decomposed` path creates child beads but keeps the decomposed parent open and execution-ineligible. That contradicts the lossless-decomposition lifecycle rule and risks leaving a half-owned parent while children should be ready work.\\n\\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:2734-2743 logs successful pre-claim decomposition then releases the parent while explicitly documenting that the parent stays open until children close.\\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:5248-5275 implements `applyPreClaimDecomposition` by setting `Extra[\\\"execution-eligible\\\"] = false` instead of closing the parent after children are created.\\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_intake_decompose_test.go:73-77 asserts the old open/ineligible behavior and does not prove children remain `ReadyExecution` through the `Parent` metadata field.\\n\\nPROPOSED FIX\\n- Update `applyPreClaimDecomposition` in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go so, after child beads are durably created, it closes the decomposed parent through the lifecycle/store API as completed by decomposition.\\n- Preserve durable traceability by recording `triage-decomposed` with generated child IDs in the event body or extra evidence.\\n- Clear parent claim metadata and heartbeat fields so a closed parent cannot remain half-owned.\\n- Preserve child readiness semantics: each child may have `Parent=\\u003cdecomposed-id\\u003e` metadata, but generated children must not depend on the decomposed parent; child-to-child ordering deps remain allowed when explicitly generated.\\n- Update/rename tests in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_intake_decompose_test.go to prove the close and readiness behavior.\\n\\nNON-SCOPE\\n- Do not change post-attempt decomposer or auto-epic decomposition behavior in this bead; those are separate children under ddx-e9542e0d.\\n- Do not implement historical tracker cleanup or the broader ddx-130cf9ab parent/ancestor dependency repair slice.\\n- Do not change intake classification semantics other than the lifecycle state applied after a successful lossless split.\\n\\nPARENT AND DEPS\\nParent: ddx-e9542e0d.\\nDeps: No deps.\\nAccept:   1. `applyPreClaimDecomposition` in `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go` closes the decomposed parent through the lifecycle/store API after child creation instead of leaving it open with `execution-eligible=false`.\\n2. The pre-claim path still records a durable `triage-decomposed` event containing generated child IDs.\\n3. Parent claim metadata and heartbeat fields are cleared on the closed decomposed parent.\\n4. `TestIntake_TooLargeDecomposed_CreatesChildrenAndClosesParent` proves children are created, the parent is closed, `triage-decomposed` is recorded, and generated children with no explicit deps are in `ReadyExecution` despite `Parent=\\u003cdecomposed-id\\u003e`.\\n5. `TestDecomposeDoesNotSelfDep` or equivalent asserts every generated child excludes the decomposed parent ID from `DepIDs()`.\\n6. `cd cli \\u0026\\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... -run 'TooLargeDecomposed|DecomposeDoesNotSelfDep|parent_ancestor_in_deps' -count=1` passes.\\n7. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\\nCreated:  2026-06-17 19:59:11\\nUpdated:  2026-06-17 19:59:11\\nspec-id: FEAT-010\\n\"}}\n.ddx/executions/20260617T195546-6fe14552/embedded/agent-codex-1781726166441906314.jsonl:65:{\"type\":\"tool_call\",\"sequence\":64,\"time\":\"2026-06-17T20:00:32.535922256Z\",\"metadata\":{\"DDX_ATTEMPT_ID\":\"20260617T195546-6fe14552\",\"DDX_BEAD_DIR\":\"/Users/erik/Projects/ddx/.ddx\",\"DDX_BEAD_ID\":\"ddx-e9542e0d\",\"DDX_MODE\":\"bead_execution\",\"GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL\":\"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-e9542e0d-20260617T195546-6fe14552/.ddx/executions/20260617T195546-6fe14552/embedded/git-global.cfg\",\"GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM\":\"/dev/null\",\"PATH\":\"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-e9542e0d-20260617T195546-6fe14552/.ddx/executions/20260617T195546-6fe14552/embedded/git-bin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/erik/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.codex/tmp/arg0/codex-arg0Yu4YDA:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/home/erik/go/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/scripts:/home/erik/.cargo/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/Coursier/bin:/home/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/home/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/.lmstudio/bin\",\"attempt_id\":\"20260617T195546-6fe14552\",\"base_rev\":\"fef4ec6c0f9b2d542f1837e943ebbba28333782b\",\"bead_id\":\"ddx-e9542e0d\",\"bundle_path\":\".ddx/executions/20260617T195546-6fe14552\",\"prompt_file\":\".ddx/executions/2026