elds already recorded by the path.\\n- Clear parent claim metadata and heartbeat fields on the closed parent.\\n- Ensure post-attempt generated children use `Parent=\\u003cdecomposed-id\\u003e` as hierarchy metadata only and are not blocked by a dependency on the decomposed parent.\\n- Update post-attempt and post-ladder tests to assert close semantics, child readiness, and `decompose-applied` child ID evidence.\\n\\nNON-SCOPE\\n- Do not change pre-claim intake decomposition or auto-epic decomposition in this bead; those are separate children under ddx-e9542e0d.\\n- Do not implement ddx-130cf9ab's broader doctor/back-edge repair work.\\n- Do not redesign historical `dead_intermediate_close` behavior for already-open containers.\\n\\nPARENT AND DEPS\\nParent: ddx-e9542e0d.\\nDeps: No deps.\\nAccept:   1. `runDecomposer` in `cli/internal/agent/recovery_decompose.go` closes the decomposed parent through the lifecycle/store API after generated child beads are created.\\n2. `decompose-applied` evidence still includes generated child IDs and existing cost/route metadata.\\n3. Parent claim metadata and heartbeat fields are cleared on the closed decomposed parent.\\n4. `TestPostAttemptTooLargeNoChanges_ClosesParentAndLeavesChildrenReady` proves post-attempt orchestrator decomposition closes the parent and generated children remain ready through the `Parent` field when they have no explicit deps.\\n5. `TestPostLadderExhaustion_TriggersDecompose_ReviewTooLarge_ClosesParent` proves the post-ladder decomposer path closes the parent and records `decompose-applied` with child IDs.\\n6. `cd cli \\u0026\\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... -run 'PostAttemptTooLargeNoChanges|PostLadderExhaustion_TriggersDecompose|DecomposeDoesNotSelfDep|parent_ancestor_in_deps' -count=1` passes.\\n7. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\\nCreated:  2026-06-17 19:59:30\\nUpdated:  2026-06-17 19:59:30\\nspec-id: FEAT-010\\n\"}}\n.ddx/executions/20260617T195546-6fe14552/embedded/agent-c